<taxonomicName id="137FD454383279CE242B3A365B051664" LSID="218083BC-F45B-5CD5-9C40-89809D95FF4D" authority="(Mandl, 1981)" baseAuthorityName="Mandl" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Cylindera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindera (Eugrapha) contorta subsp. valdenbergi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="contorta" subGenus="Eugrapha" subSpecies="valdenbergi">Cylindera (Eugrapha) contorta (Fischer von Waldheim, 1828), ssp. valdenbergi (Mandl, 1981)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3B38CE1128A865BE31831811DA3EBEA" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="1BE2CDD12699219E42C9C2DA7C594F5E" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="723B9100960DBEF9E4D7C8CE1DB8974E" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">
In the southern Levant found exclusively in sandy shore habitats along the Mediterranean Sea. Larval development takes place a few centimeters above the mean sea level, just above where most of the waves break (
<bibRefCitation id="D736994DB230C4804CAEA5C8546C4E80" author="Valdenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="38 - 48" refId="B105" refString="Valdenberg, A, 1983. The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew). Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center 1: 38 - 48" title="The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew)." volume="1" year="1983">Valdenberg 1983</bibRefCitation>
), though larval holes are occasionally flooded by seawater. The nominate subspecies is found in both coastal and inland habitats (
<bibRefCitation id="7B4B9FF19D5E420E02970438C6BD0E6F" author="Cassola, F" journalOrPublisher="Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne" pageId="39" pageNumber="82" pagination="193 - 214" refId="B30" refString="Cassola, F, Jaskula, R, 2004. Materials to the knowledge of the tiger beetles of Romania (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 73: 193 - 214" title="Materials to the knowledge of the tiger beetles of Romania (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="73" year="2004">
Cassola and 
<normalizedToken id="BAAFC1F6DBB2C089DF9B93FB66601733" originalValue="Jaskuła">Jaskula</normalizedToken>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
). Attracted by light (own observation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4A8D74BFE0FAB4ACE5366E7E84C011E6" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="39864B570DAFB5AF49F6BE2C4069356B" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="08B6B2E0D5A1772956F5EEBB115886C4" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">
Adults from the beginning of May until mid-November (
<bibRefCitation id="C07F1CF986BDC88001407B2BC881B211" author="Valdenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="38 - 48" refId="B105" refString="Valdenberg, A, 1983. The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew). Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center 1: 38 - 48" title="The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew)." volume="1" year="1983">Valdenberg 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Few adults also from March onwards (
<bibRefCitation id="EB57E807C93F1F54E27231297A1D3028" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" author="Matalin, AV" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="115 - 160" refId="B82" refString="Matalin, AV, Chikatunov, VI, 2016. The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands. ZooKeys 578: 115 - 160, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" title="The tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelinae) of Israel and adjacent lands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.578.7383" volume="578" year="2016">Matalin and Chikatunov 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A08B98150D09C9F8A90B4FB08E7B173C" author="Nussbaum, Y" journalOrPublisher="YES Quarterly" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 15" refId="B87" refString="Nussbaum, Y, 1987. Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). YES Quarterly 4: 7 - 15" title="Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="4" year="1987">Nussbaum 1987</bibRefCitation>
). The larvae overwinter mostly as second and third instars (and rarely also first instars). Egg laying begins immediately with the appearance of the adults in spring, and in certain years a few individuals may complete an entire life-cycle in the same summer, though most do not (
<bibRefCitation id="C5E948E51E89022C3F09DA525C93D3FF" author="Valdenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="38 - 48" refId="B105" refString="Valdenberg, A, 1983. The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew). Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center 1: 38 - 48" title="The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew)." volume="1" year="1983">Valdenberg 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8B1E6AE0F22D0FEEE29D45820B8CDEBF" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="05AC8C0CD39F0D6A550D039A3A7CB532" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Distribution range.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00A4453ECC632684F40E0582B81EFEF0" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">
The nominate form is found from south-eastern Europe (Romania and Ukraine) and Asia Minor to Central Asia and China. The 
<taxonomicName id="87AC631A437B5F740A33F51C6656C7D3" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Cephalota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephalota subsp. valdenbergi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="contorta" subSpecies="valdenbergi">Cephalota subspecies valdenbergi</taxonomicName>
is patchily located in a small area along the Mediterranean coast from western Egypt to northern Israel (
<bibRefCitation id="76F04D590EFFD544605DE50493BAFB43" author="Horn, W" journalOrPublisher="Bundesamt fuer Naturschutz, Bonn" pageId="42" pageNumber="85" refId="B61" refString="Horn, W, 1931. Zur Kenntnis der Cicindelen-Fauna von Cypern, Syrien, Sizilien, Aegypten und Sued-Griechenland (insbesondere der geographischen Verbreitung der Arten Cicindela aphrodisia Baudi, C. campestris suffriani Loew, C. contorta Fisch. und dorsata Br., sowie C. aulica Dej.). Bulletin de la Societe Royale Entomologique d'Egypte Seance du 17 November: 157-163." title="Zur Kenntnis der Cicindelen-Fauna von Cypern, Syrien, Sizilien, Aegypten und Sued-Griechenland (insbesondere der geographischen Verbreitung der Arten Cicindela aphrodisia Baudi, C. campestris suffriani Loew, C. contorta Fisch. und dorsata Br., sowie C. aulica Dej.). Bulletin de la Societe Royale Entomologique d'Egypte Seance du 17 November: 157 - 163." year="1931">Horn 1931</bibRefCitation>
, Mandl 1981). The nominate form does not occur along the Mediterranean coast (
<bibRefCitation id="FBAA5FA90DD9C2542DF016FAE1ED7F05" author="Wiesner, J" journalOrPublisher="Erna Bauer, Keltern" pageId="45" pageNumber="88" refId="B114" refString="Wiesner, J, 1992. Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world. Erna Bauer, Keltern" title="Checklist of the tiger beetles of the world." year="1992">Wiesner 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19765C859665D8D9F9A54C497FFCBA41" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C4E8C232AA92EA673E3B1F9F21794834" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Distribution in the southern Levant.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38C737FA39DABBFF504D10049ECA53B6" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">
In Egypt around Abu Qir, Maadia and Ras el Bar (
<bibRefCitation id="B5051AF8C6DDCD6959BFFD8700DA1AF5" author="Abdel-Dayem, MS" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Entomological Society of Egypt" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="193 - 217" refId="B1" refString="Abdel-Dayem, MS, El-Haewagri, MSA, Yassan, SA, 2003. A review of the Egyptian species of tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelidae). Bulletin of the Entomological Society of Egypt 80: 193 - 217" title="A review of the Egyptian species of tiger beetles (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Cicindelidae)." volume="80" year="2003">Abdel-Dayem et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="933A40CD1F19404D48A0A15ED0D0C263" author="Alfieri, A" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Egypte" pageId="38" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 361" refId="B5" refString="Alfieri, A, 1976. The Coleoptera of Egypt. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Egypte 5: 1 - 361" title="The Coleoptera of Egypt." volume="5" year="1976">Alfieri 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3A88184A2D15AF3BA8856043B626EE8B" author="Horn, W" journalOrPublisher="Bundesamt fuer Naturschutz, Bonn" pageId="42" pageNumber="85" refId="B61" refString="Horn, W, 1931. Zur Kenntnis der Cicindelen-Fauna von Cypern, Syrien, Sizilien, Aegypten und Sued-Griechenland (insbesondere der geographischen Verbreitung der Arten Cicindela aphrodisia Baudi, C. campestris suffriani Loew, C. contorta Fisch. und dorsata Br., sowie C. aulica Dej.). Bulletin de la Societe Royale Entomologique d'Egypte Seance du 17 November: 157-163." title="Zur Kenntnis der Cicindelen-Fauna von Cypern, Syrien, Sizilien, Aegypten und Sued-Griechenland (insbesondere der geographischen Verbreitung der Arten Cicindela aphrodisia Baudi, C. campestris suffriani Loew, C. contorta Fisch. und dorsata Br., sowie C. aulica Dej.). Bulletin de la Societe Royale Entomologique d'Egypte Seance du 17 November: 157 - 163." year="1931">Horn 1931</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0929874CF36FEDEF6DBE40E097C319C6" author="Mandl, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Basiliensia" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="167 - 182" refId="B80" refString="Mandl, K, 1981a. Neue Coleopteren-Taxa vom Nahen bis zum Fernen Osten (Col. Cicindelidae, Carabidae und Chrysomelidae). Entomologica Basiliensia 6: 167 - 182" title="Neue Coleopteren-Taxa vom Nahen bis zum Fernen Osten (Col. Cicindelidae, Carabidae und Chrysomelidae)." volume="6" year="1981 a">Mandl 1981a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1E14C4694D95BD6F91FA6382A6F9801A" author="Nussbaum, Y" journalOrPublisher="YES Quarterly" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="7 - 15" refId="B87" refString="Nussbaum, Y, 1987. Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). YES Quarterly 4: 7 - 15" title="Tiger beetles of Israel and Sinai (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." volume="4" year="1987">Nussbaum 1987</bibRefCitation>
). In Israel from Bat Yam to Akko, though the Bat Yam population is thought to be extinct since several decades (
<bibRefCitation id="0964F21F293677DB02161370F591C8A3" author="Valdenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" pagination="38 - 48" refId="B105" refString="Valdenberg, A, 1983. The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew). Shappirit - Journal of the Israel Entomology Center 1: 38 - 48" title="The tiger beetles family. General survey of the family and key to species in Israel and Sinai (in Hebrew)." volume="1" year="1983">Valdenberg 1983</bibRefCitation>
; own observation).
</paragraph>
