<subSubSection id="CE8370A5899C990DC53E6DA27A35495E" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="4F35B29DCC78D25975AFA3B3B0F2DF2E" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B09E02D55E8091D1BA2153957A1D97A" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">
<bibRefCitation id="5ADBBB59FFB038DA3B37D4F7205E65BD" author="Mandl, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Basiliensia" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="167 - 182" refId="B80" refString="Mandl, K, 1981a. Neue Coleopteren-Taxa vom Nahen bis zum Fernen Osten (Col. Cicindelidae, Carabidae und Chrysomelidae). Entomologica Basiliensia 6: 167 - 182" title="Neue Coleopteren-Taxa vom Nahen bis zum Fernen Osten (Col. Cicindelidae, Carabidae und Chrysomelidae)." volume="6" year="1981 a">Mandl (1981a)</bibRefCitation>
described the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="4D972DE271B3A02934CB8C7EDC631119" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Cylindera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindera valdenbergi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdenbergi">
<emphasis id="5452079565E9B3116E7BB28A96753CD9" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Cylindera valdenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken id="796B3A32EAA25379897B3089E5C118E6" originalValue="Ma’agan">Ma'agan</normalizedToken>
Michael as a subspecies. It is characterized by the excessive pale elytral pattern (Figs 
<figureCitation id="7738BD455FFC45A120947C56E9C6A24F" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figures 29 - 32. Cylindera (sub-) species: 29 C. contorta s. str. (male) 30 C. rectangularis (female) 31 C. contorta valdenbergi (male) 32 C. contorta valdenbergi (female)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figures29-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183617" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FAFAFE48E6A0AE8C34FD8A52B0BD7861" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figures 29 - 32. Cylindera (sub-) species: 29 C. contorta s. str. (male) 30 C. rectangularis (female) 31 C. contorta valdenbergi (male) 32 C. contorta valdenbergi (female)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figures29-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183617" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">32</figureCitation>
), though there is some variation in the pattern between individuals. However, the pale elytral coloration differs even within the nominate form strongly. Some populations from the Caspian Sea show similar elytral pattern as 
<taxonomicName id="3E81CEA7DE185236810EB73D854134D4" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Cylindera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindera valdenbergi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdenbergi">
<emphasis id="2A0D6D247C45A24BB8734A5EA113EDAF" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Cylindera valdenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C2A14CA9F6803C8514E4BEBD220C4AA" author="Mandl, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Basiliensia" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" pagination="167 - 182" refId="B80" refString="Mandl, K, 1981a. Neue Coleopteren-Taxa vom Nahen bis zum Fernen Osten (Col. Cicindelidae, Carabidae und Chrysomelidae). Entomologica Basiliensia 6: 167 - 182" title="Neue Coleopteren-Taxa vom Nahen bis zum Fernen Osten (Col. Cicindelidae, Carabidae und Chrysomelidae)." volume="6" year="1981 a">Mandl 1981a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="AD896A323345C946CB2595DD5561F2E2" author="Werner, K" journalOrPublisher="Science Nat, Venette" pageId="44" pageNumber="87" refId="B110" refString="Werner, K, 1992. Cicindelidae 2. Science Nat, Venette" title="Cicindelidae 2." year="1992">Werner 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Mandl mentioned in his description small differences in the copulatory pieces of the median lobe of aedeagus. As we believe this character is still not sufficiently studied. But the material we studied let us assume that 
<taxonomicName id="3B27DF6D9EF24193BB0726A67234D92C" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Cylindera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindera valdenbergi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdenbergi">
<emphasis id="987F7395E8AA968132FEEB463E1EB715" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Cylindera valdenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the nominate subspecies at least in the proportion and shape of the pronotum and the elytra (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9824FD6D9AFE77536534AD1FB0D7DB97" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figures 29 - 32. Cylindera (sub-) species: 29 C. contorta s. str. (male) 30 C. rectangularis (female) 31 C. contorta valdenbergi (male) 32 C. contorta valdenbergi (female)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figures29-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183617" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">29</figureCitation>
). We recommend conducting a detailed study, including morphometric and molecular methods, to clarify the status of both taxa. 
<bibRefCitation id="A94CBF6629FF913BCF1BCD142DAAB6CF" author="Ptashkovsky, Y" journalOrPublisher="Cornell University Press, Ithaca and London" pageId="43" pageNumber="86" refId="B93" refString="Ptashkovsky, Y, 2013. Beetles of Israel. self-published, Tel Aviv." title="Beetles of Israel. self-published, Tel Aviv." year="2013">Ptashkovsky (2013)</bibRefCitation>
includes a photograph of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="45E6C6E76D88F07AF1AB9E25C284A9F8" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Lophyra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lophyra contorta subsp. valdenbergi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="contorta" subSpecies="valdenbergi">
<emphasis id="62A92B7D886A9F2331F94FC871EF650A" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Lophyra contorta valdenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, but the shown specimen belongs to the nominate subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="28A5AF230529F5FDEF053C0CB211EB4B" baseAuthorityName="Fischer von Waldheim" baseAuthorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Cylindera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindera contorta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contorta">
<emphasis id="1ADA8A3D26D929653A02D4C551EA72F3" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">Cylindera contorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A4A55E8D4CF07DDDB9E84B51EF1C58E0" captionStart="Figures 29–32" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figures 29 - 32. Cylindera (sub-) species: 29 C. contorta s. str. (male) 30 C. rectangularis (female) 31 C. contorta valdenbergi (male) 32 C. contorta valdenbergi (female)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figures29-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183617" pageId="28" pageNumber="71">29</figureCitation>
), and with all probability the photographed specimen was not collected in Israel.
</paragraph>
<caption id="928D23F13B56FF952833481AED3752AA" ID-Zenodo-Dep="1223956" doi="10.3897/zookeys.734.21989.figure44" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/183625" pageId="28" pageNumber="71" start="Figure 44" startId="F20">
